        <h2>Projects</h2>
        <p>As a product manager who codes, I build simple tools to solve problems and understand technology better. Here are some of my experiments:</p>

        <div class="project-card">
            <h3>NSE Corporate Filing Actions Bot</h3>
            <p>A practical tool that automates downloading NSE's corporate filing data. Built this to understand:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>How AI agents can automate browser interactions</li>
                <li>Scheduling automated tasks with GitHub Actions - haven't figured this out yet</li>
            </ul>
            <a href="https://github.com/BharatBheesetti/NSE_Corp_Filing_Actions_bot" class="project-link">View Project →</a>
        </div>

        <div class="project-card">
            <h3>Neural Network from Scratch</h3>
            <p>Built a basic MNIST digit classifier using raw Python to understand:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Core concepts behind neural networks</li>
                <li>How modern ML frameworks work under the hood</li>
                <li>Achieved ~76% accuracy without using numpy or ML libraries</li>
            </ul>
            <a href="https://github.com/BharatBheesetti/MNIST-Classifier-with-only-Python" class="project-link">View Project →</a>
        </div>

        <div class="project-card">
            <h3>Scribe - Audio Transcription Tool</h3>
            <p>A simple desktop app that records and transcribes audio. Built because:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Wanted a local, private, secure app for Windows.</li>
                <li>see what python app dev looked like</li>
                <li>Create a practical tool for note-taking</li>
            </ul>
            <a href="https://github.com/BharatBheesetti/Scribe" class="project-link">View Project →</a>
        </div>
    </div>

